Basic.desc: Basic test vectors use the simplest possible inputs. These inputs often overlap with inputs from standards and RFCs. One goal of such test vectors is to simply detect distinct algorithms.

EdgeCaseRemainder.desc: The test vector contains a ciphertext where decryption enconters edge case values if Chinese remaindering is being used to speed up decryption.

InvalidCiphertext.desc: The test vector contains a ciphertext that is invalid. The invalidity of the ciphertext can (and should) be determined before attempting to decrypt. Hence padding attacks should not be possible with this kind of modifications.

ModifiedPadding.desc: The test vector contains a ciphertext where the padding has been modified.
ModifiedPadding.effect: Accepting RSA ciphertexts with modified padding may allow chosen ciphertext attacks.

NonAsciiLabel.desc: The label in this test vector is not a valid ASCII encoding. Some libraries are restricted to labels that are ASCII strings. Hence such libraries cannot be tested with this test vector.

NonUtf8Label.desc: The label in this test vector is not a valid UTF-8 encoding. This prevents that libraries expexpecting strings as parameters from using the test vector.

Pseudorandom.desc: The test vector has been generated pseudorandomly.
